                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12939953" author="gtully" created="Wed, 9 Jul 2008 15:13:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the recieving Transportconnection that initiates the duplex network bridge on the target broker is not stopped and hense not unregistered from JMX. Directing the bridge stop through this connection when the bridge is duplex fixes the problem. Test case and fix attached in this patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12939947" author="rajdavies" created="Wed, 9 Jul 2008 19:16:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch applied in SVN revision 675314&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12939951" author="rajdavies" created="Thu, 10 Jul 2008 09:09:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test case doesn&apos;t work consistenty for iterations of start/stop greater than 2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12939943" author="rajdavies" created="Thu, 10 Jul 2008 09:27:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed by revision 675484&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12939911" author="dave_stanley" created="Thu, 10 Jul 2008 14:55:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tracking..&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This also resolves NPE in DemandForwardingBridge&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
